properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 17 at 7:24AM EST until January 19 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Cleveland OH
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 knots with gusts up to 50 knots and
waves 9 to 14 feet possible.

* WHERE...Portions of central and eastern Lake Erie.

* WHEN...Saturday afternoon through Sunday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING
